# E2E: `enozunu summon` materializes a selected source into its Claude-native path.
#
# Uses a `local` provider source to keep the baseline happy path free of git
# setup: this case is about materialization into the Claude-native path, not
# about source resolution. Git-source resolution is covered per selector in
# summon_git_selectors.repor, which stays offline by building a repository in
# the case workspace and referencing it with a `file://` URL.

case "summon materializes a local skill source" {
  write <"sources/demo-skill/SKILL.md"> ```
    ---
    name: demo-skill
    description: demo skill for the summon happy path
    ---

    # Demo Skill
    ```
  write <"enozunu.kdl"> ```
    enozunu config-version=1 {
      provider {
        skills {
          skill "demo-skill" {
            local {
              path "sources/demo-skill"
            }
          }
        }
      }
      consumer {
        claude {
          use-skills "demo-skill"
        }
      }
    }
    ```
  $ enozunu summon
  assert {
    exit 0
    stdout contains "materialized"
    file <".claude/skills/demo-skill/SKILL.md"> contains "demo skill for the summon happy path"
    file <".enozunu/provenance.json"> contains "demo-skill"
  }
}
